esserung entsprechender Aushandlungsverfahren beizutragen. Es geht um die Frage: Wer und was muss wie berücksichtigt werden?  a»More or less?« Ecological growth criticism opposes destructive dynamics of modern societies of industry and excess that endanger a good life. Concepts of sustainable development often adhere to the modern promises of more far too optimistically. But merely turning towards »less« yields no better answers, either. Instead, sustainable development requires the continuous search for appropriate means and ends. Stephan Lorenz shows that chances for this lie in democratizing the search processes. The social sciences are given the task to contribute to the improvement of the respective negotiation processes. The question is: Who and what must be taken into account?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEconomic developmentxEnvironmental aspects. 0aSustainable developmentxSocial aspects. 4aGesellschaftstheorie. 4aMaterielle Kultur. 4aNachhaltige Entwicklung. 4aNachhaltigkeit. 4aNatur. 4aSoziologie. 4aUmweltsoziologie. 4aWirtschaft. 4aWirtschaftssoziologie. 4aÖkologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aEconomic Sociology.  aEconomy.  aEnvironmental Sociology.  aMaterial Culture.  aNature.  aSocial Theory.  aSociology.  aSustainability.  aSustainable Growth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2014z9783110370416oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014z9783111025223oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gr